'''Nellcor''' is a brand of pulse oximetry systems sold by the [[Covidien]] Corporation, formerly a division of Tyco International.

== History  ==

1981: Nellcor was started by Dr. William '''NE'''w, Jack '''LL'''oyd and Jim '''COR'''enman in [[Hayward, California]] to develop and market [[Pulse oximetry | pulse oximetry systems]]

1983: Nellcor introduced its [[Pulse oximetry|pulse oximeter]] and quickly wins market share from [[Biox]] 

1995: Nellcor expands into  respiratory-related products by acquiring Puritan-Bennett. Company renamed Nellcor Puritan Bennett.<ref>http://www.nellcor.com/news/history.aspx</ref>

1997: Nellcor Puritan Bennett is purchased by [[Mallinckrodt Incorporated|Mallinckrodt Inc.]] <ref>http://www.nellcor.com/news/history.aspx</ref>

2000: [[Mallinckrodt Incorporated|Mallinckrodt]] is purchased by [[Tyco International|Tyco International Ltd.]]. Tyco established Nellcor and Puritan Bennett as separate businesses under the Tyco Healthcare umbrella.<ref>http://www.nellcor.com/news/history.aspx</ref>

2007: [[Covidien]] becomes a publicly traded company after being spun out of Tyco.<ref>[[Covidien]]</ref> Continues to market the Nellcor brand,<ref>http://respiratorysolutions.covidien.com/PatientMonitoring/tabid/67/Default.aspx</ref> which dominates the market together with [[Masimo]] <ref>[http://services.corporate-ir.net/SEC/Document.Service?id=P3VybD1odHRwOi8vaXIuaW50Lndlc3RsYXdidXNpbmVzcy5jb20vZG9jdW1lbnQvdjEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNS0xMS0wMzY5NzAvZG9jL01hc2ltb0NvcnBvcmF0aW9uXzEwS18yMDExMDIxNi5wZGYmdHlwZT0yJmZuPU1hc2ltb0NvcnBvcmF0aW9uXzEwS18yMDExMDIxNi5wZGY= Masimo SEC Filing 10-K for 2010]</ref>

== Main Products ==
[[Pulse oximetry]] is based on a technology originally developed in 1972, by Takuo Aoyagi and Michio Kishi at [[Nihon Kohden]] using the ratio of red to infrared light absorption of pulsating components at the measuring site and first commercialized by [[Biox|BIOX/Ohmeda]] in 1981.<ref>http://www.oximetry.org/pulseox/history.htm</ref>

